obvious.data
Interface Network

All Superinterfaces:
Adaptable, Data, Graph<Node,Edge>
public interface Network
extends Graph<Node,Edge>

Network is a subclass of the generic Graph interface using for nodes and edges classes that derived from Tuple: Node and Edge. Currently, all Obvious bindings use this interface to modelize graphs.

Version:
$Revision$
Author:
Jean-Daniel Fekete

beginEdit

void beginEdit(int col)
               throws ObviousException
Indicates the beginning of a column edit.

This function could be used to create a context when a large number of modifications happens to a same column to avoid time wasting with plenty of notifications. In this context, TableListeners could ignore notifications if wanted.

Parameters:
col - column index
Throws:
ObviousException - if edition is not supported.

endEdit

boolean endEdit(int col)
                throws ObviousException
Indicates the end of a column edit.

This function indicates, if notifications were disabled, that now they are enabled. It could also call a mechanism to replay the sequence of ignored events if wanted.

Parameters:
col - column index
Returns:
true if transaction succeed
Throws:
ObviousException - if edition is not supported.
